description:
&lt;p&gt;The ventricular assist device team based at Freeman Hospital are seeking to appoint a band 7 nurse practitioner to join this dynamic team, with an international and national reputation within the field of MCS. The team is aligned with the advanced heart failure multi- disciplinary team providing care for patients pre and post ventricular assist device implantation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant should possess knowledge of MCS therapy and advanced heart failure. They will be expected to work autonomously co-ordinating care within the inpatient and outpatient settings, as well as being an integral part of the MDT. There is an expectation that the successful candidate will be involved in service improvement, audit and research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37 hours 30 minutes/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nicola Robinson Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address nicola.robinsonsmith@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
